<p><a href="/wiki/Cognitive_science" title="Cognitive science">Cognitive science</a> and <a href="/wiki/Theoretical_linguistics" title="Theoretical linguistics">linguistic theory</a> have played an important role in providing empirical research into the <a href="/wiki/Writing_process" title="Writing process">writing process</a> and serving the teaching of composition. As composition theories, there is some dispute concerning the appropriateness of tying these two schools of thought together into one theory of <a href="/wiki/Composition_studies" title="Composition studies">composition</a>. However, their empirical basis for research and ties to the process theory of composition and cognitive science can be thought to warrant  some connection.
</p>
<div id="toc" class="toc"><input type="checkbox" role="button" id="toctogglecheckbox" class="toctogglecheckbox" style="display:none" /><div class="toctitle" lang="en" dir="ltr"><h2>Contents</h2><span class="toctogglespan"><label class="toctogglelabel" for="toctogglecheckbox"></label></span></div>
